        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 7 at 7:06PM CDT until August 7 at 7:30PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northeast
of Alamo, or 14 miles south of Crosby, moving east at 25 mph.
Additional strong to severe strongs extended southwest to Grenora.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Crosby, Grenora, Alamo, Writing Rock State Historical Site, Hanks
City, Zahl, Appam, Hanks, and Corinth.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
